<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 9:27PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central
Sherman, southeastern Dallam and north central Hartley Counties
through 1000 PM CDT...
At 927 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles northeast of Ware, or 15 miles northwest of Dalhart, moving
southeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Dalhart, Ware and Conlen.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CDT for
the Panhandle of Texas.</instruction>
